Salaire compétitif selon expérience.

Nous avons actuellement des opportunités excitantes pour les pilotes qui cherchent à faire progresser leur carrière, car nous sommes à la recherche de capitaines pour le Bell 212 et le Bell 412.
Responsabilités:
Exercer les fonctions de Capitaine selon les standards d’opération de la compagnie;
Exercer les fonctions de pilote VFR lorsque requis;
Assumer toutes autres responsabilités connexes au poste.
Qualifications
Détenir une licence commerciale valide de pilote d’hélicoptère de Transport Canada;
Détenir l’autorisation de travailler au Canada, ce poste n'est pas disponible pour un parrainage;
3000 heures de vol sur hélicoptère (500 heures PAC multi-moteurs) et endossement sur B212 et/ou B412.
2 années d’expérience sur des opérations de vol aux instruments;
Détenir un PPC valide de pilote aux commandes sur type.
Accréditation de vol aux instruments de groupe IV de Transport Canada;
Posséder une certification de vol de nuit sans restriction;
Selon le lieu du contrat, le candidat doit pouvoir se rendre aux États-Unis pour suivre une formation;
Accepter des affectations à différents endroits, selon les besoins;
Être orienté vers le service client et avoir l’esprit d’équipe;
Avoir de bonnes aptitudes en communication et une attitude positive;
Expérience LVN, un atout;
Compétences et expérience en élingue de précision seront considérés comme un atout majeur.
Expérience dans l'Arctique - serait considérée comme un atout.

Competitive salary according to experience.

The AME will be reporting to the Maintenance Manager and his duties include:
Planning and performing aircraft maintenance;
Ensuring that all replacement parts are inspected and properly certified prior to installation;
Organizing and housekeeping of the hangar facility;
Assuring compliance with all company policies and procedures;
Travelling to various work locations and environments as required;
Performing related duties as assigned by supervisor.
Qualifications
Must hold a valid Transport Canada M1 and/or M2 AME licence;
Must have the legal right to work in Canada, this position is not available for sponsorship;
Hold or have held Aircraft Certification Authority (ACA) on the AS350B2 and/or AS355N and/or B206;
Holding ACA on other types of CHL aircrafts would be a definite asset;
Organized and self-starter;
Customer focus, good communication skills and positive attitude;
Must live in Sept-Îles or be willing to relocate to the area;
Ability to accept away-from-base assignments, at the customer request.
Additional Information
Remuneration:
Competitive salary according to experience.
Working for Canadian Helicopters is:
A unique occasion to grow professionally in a dynamic environment full of opportunities.
Working with passionate, committed people who enjoy surpassing themselves.
Being part of an organizational culture based on fundamental principles.
Having an employer of choice offering competitive working conditions.
We offer a flexible benefits program that include a complete dental and medical protection, life insurance, short and long-term disability insurance and a pension plan, depending on employment status.
Canadian Helicopters Limited is committed to employment equity and diversity and encourages applications from women, Indigenous people, persons with disabilities and visible minorities.

Responsibilities:
Deliver ground school lectures,
Deliver FTD lessons, and
Carry out maintenance test flights as required.
Qualifications
Licence:
TC Commercial Pilot’s Licence;
Foreign Commercial Pilot’s Licence;
current/former RCAF helicopter pilot; or
current/former foreign military qualification;
B206 and/or B412 endorsement are an asset;
Multi-engine rotary-wing experience an asset;
Able to obtain a TC medical for flying positions (non-flying positions do not require a TC medical);
TC Instructor Rating;
This requirement is waived for former RCAF pilots and foreign military instructors in certain specific circumstances:
TC Class IV Instrument Rating and Night Vision Goggle experience preferable;
Good oral and written communication skills in English, French language skills an asset;
Additional Information
Working for Canadian Helicopters is:
A unique occasion to grow professionally in a dynamic environment full of opportunities.
Working with passionate, committed people who enjoy surpassing themselves.
Being part of an organizational culture based on fundamental principles.
Having an employer of choice offering competitive working conditions.
We offer a flexible benefits program including comprehensive medical and dental coverage, life insurance, short- and long-term disability insurance and a pension fund plan.
Canadian Helicopters Limited is committed to employment equity and diversity and encourages applications from women, Indigenous people, and visible minorities.
For more information we invite you to visit our website:
www.canadianhelicopters.com
Follow us on LinkedIn:
https://ca.linkedin.com/company/canadian-helicopters-limited

NHV Group is a European based helicopter service provider, specialised in business-to-business helicopter services both offshore & onshore.
As a Mechanic at our base in Lanvéoc, you'll join a small but highly skilled and enthusiast team, committed to excellence.
Responsibilities & areas
Maintenance tasks on aircraft and components in accordance with issued work orders, applicable manuals, and approved maintenance data.
Carry out activities such as:
Disassembly & reassembly
Rectify defects
Component replacements and system adjustments
Ensure all safety regulations and procedures are followed at all times;
Immediately report safety hazards or mandatory occurrences via the NHV occurrence reporting system;
Follow all MOE procedures and notify the Chief Engineer/Maintenance Lead if instructions or processes are unclear, incomplete, or ambiguous;
Record all performed maintenance accurately and clearly in the work file;
Raise defect entries or non-routine tasks for any findings discovered during inspections;
Support Licensed Engineers during troubleshooting and functional checks;
Maintain a clean, safe, and organized working environment, including proper care of tools and ground equipment;
Contribute to a flexible and efficient planning;
Help ensure that planned maintenance is completed within appropriate timeframes to support operational needs.
Skills & Experience
At NHV, we are dedicated to deliver excellence in the helicopter world.
With a commitment to safety, innovation, and customer centricity, we provide reliable services that support a wide range of missions.
We expect you to contribute to this level of service and trust that you will bring the following competencies to strengthen the team:
Good communication skills to work together with direct colleagues, store keepers, CAMO engineers, etc. and for handover work;
Demonstrated experience in base and line maintenance operations;
Strong understanding of EASA regulations and safety protocols;
Accuracy and reliability;
Flexibility;
Easily combine working in a team and the ability to work independently.
Languages:
English & French: fluent, professional level (speaking, reading, writing);
Only candidates who meet the legal right to live and work in France will be considered for this position.
What we offer
Step into an exciting career in an international helicopter services company that combines a youthful spirit with over 25 years of industry expertise.
When you join our team, you can count on a permanent (indefinite) contract and a competitive salary package, supplemented with meal & gift vouchers, etc.

NHV Group is a European based helicopter service provider, specialised in business-to-business helicopter services both offshore & onshore.
We’re looking for an experienced B2 engineer to join our dedicated team at our base in Lanvéoc, France. You'll be part of a small but highly skilled and enthusiast team, committed to excellence.
Responsibilities & areas
Perform base & line maintenance on aircraft and components as per work orders;
Perform effective troubleshooting based on pilot reports and system indications;
Ensure that all maintenance tasks are carried out, following all approved maintenance data, procedures (MOE), and airworthiness regulations;
Ensure that all maintenance is completed within the appropriate time scales to have a serviceable aircraft that meets the operational need;
Accurately certify completed tasks and ensure proper documentation in the work pack;
Ensure proper handling, segregation, and documentation of removed/installed components;
Adhere to safety standards; report hazards and occurrences via the NHV reporting system;
Ensure briefing & debriefing of the Chief Engineer and/or Maintenance Lead; Report daily on the maintenance situation; Inform and update the CE/ML on the maintenance situation;
Certify B2 category maintenance activities in accordance with the regulations;
Work independently when performing in a less controlled environment and take initiative to improve work, show flexibility within the team to complete tasks within appropriate time scales.
Skills & Experience
At NHV, we are dedicated to deliver excellence in the helicopter world. With a commitment to safety, innovation, and customer centricity, we provide reliable services that support a wide range of missions. We expect you to be willing to contribute to this level of service and trust that you will bring the following competencies to strengthen the team:
EASA Part 66 B2 License (upload copy when applying);
AS365 N3 type rated;
Good communication skills to work together with direct colleagues, store keepers, CAMO engineers, etc. and for handover work;
Demonstrated experience in base and line maintenance operations;
Strong understanding of EASA regulations and safety protocols;
Accuracy and reliability;
Flexibility;
Easily combine working in a team and the ability to work independently.
Languages:
English & French: fluent, professional level (speaking, reading, writing);
Only candidates who meet the legal right to live and work in France will be considered for this position.
What we offer
Step into an exciting career in an international helicopter services company that combines a youthful spirit with over 25 years of industry expertise.
When you join our team, you can count on a permanent (indefinite) contract and a competitive salary package, supplemented with meal & gift vouchers, etc.

